verbose_text: Color flow Doppler imaging is necessary for the evaluation of pelvic vessels but is often limited due to the intrinsic difficulty in plainly outlining the pelvic structures; US imaging in general is also strictly dependent on the technical expertise of the investigator and restricted by patient 's obesity and bowel gas [XREF_BIBR].
